# Cloudflare Pages redirects. Rules are matched top-to-bottom, FIRST match wins —
# so every specific 301 MUST sit above the catch-all SPA rewrite at the bottom.

# ── DNS-cutover 301s (see docs/runbooks/website-dns-cutover.md) ───────────────
# Old Toast single-page site at the apex bunkerokc.com. Its only real server path
# besides "/" was "/home"; the #AboutUs / #OurProducts / #Events / #Contact /
# #Directions links were client-side fragments that never reach the server, so they
# can't be 301'd individually. "/" already resolves to the new home (the section
# those anchors lived on), so no rule is needed for them.
/home       /       301
/home/*     /       301

# Old bunkerclubokc.com WordPress blog — the FOUNDERS' domain, NOT ours to move
# (SSL expired; see the runbook). These fire only if that domain is ever pointed at
# this Pages project. Included so the richest legacy URLs land somewhere sensible if
# it is. Both trailing-slash forms are covered (WordPress served the slashed form).
/the-legendary-oklahoma-citys-bunker-club    /about    301
/the-legendary-oklahoma-citys-bunker-club/   /about    301
/the-bunker-clubs-uniqueness                 /about    301
/the-bunker-clubs-uniqueness/                /about    301
/the-signatured-manhattan-project-drink      /menu     301
/the-signatured-manhattan-project-drink/     /menu     301

# ── SPA fallback (MUST stay last) ────────────────────────────────────────────
/*  /index.html  200
